                            <comment id="199950" author="schamp" created="Thu, 22 Jun 2017 11:50:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I am seeing this error message when I mount a ZFS OST on a system without ldiskfs installed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;{{# mount -t lustre ost02/ost02 /mnt/ost02&lt;br/&gt;
mount.lustre FATAL: unhandled/unloaded fs type 0 &apos;ext3&apos;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;rpm -q lustre&lt;br/&gt;
lustre-2.9.59_32_g62bc3af-1.el7.centos.x86_64&lt;br/&gt;
}}&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;


&lt;p&gt;This is today&apos;s multi-rail branch, which was just synced with master.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;re-open, new ticket, or is this a feature of my not having an entry in ldev.conf?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
